data.body:
When deactivating packages defining **app menus** containing menu items of type `separator`, those items don't get removed. I don't have this issue with **context menus**, however.

![menu_item_separator_issue](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5003795/11985314/1a532e3e-a9cc-11e5-831d-5ff961c8e127.gif)

Neither of bundled packages provided Packages menu entries with separators, so for demo I've generated and trimmed down a new menu-only package with menu.cson containing this object:

``` coffee
'menu': [
  {
    'label': 'Packages'
    'submenu': [
      'label': 'my-package'
      'submenu': [
        { 'label': 'Toggle my-package1', 'command': 'command-palette:toggle' },
        { 'type': 'separator' },
        { 'label': 'Toggle my-package2', 'command': 'command-palette:toggle' }
      ]
    ]
  }
]
```

**Atom version:** 1.4.0-beta3-385721a (observed the same issue under the stable 1.3.0 I've recently updated from)
**OS and version:** openSUSE 13.1 (Bottle) (i586) | KDE 4.11.5

Found this issue when using Atom for an Ember CLI project. 

Atom Version 1.3.2
## Steps to reproduce

![screen shot 2015-12-22 at 15 50 48](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1667141/11959163/d0940cea-a8c3-11e5-9a10-fe164c0c2f5a.png)
- The above folder structure. These command can create the structure: 

```
mkdir -p project/controllers/test/;
mkdir -p project/routes/test/;
mkdir -p project/controllers/test2;
touch project/controllers/test/index.js;
touch project/controllers/test2/index.js;
touch project/routes/test/index.js;
```
- Click controllers/test/index.js
- Click routes/test/index.js
- Click controllers/test2/index.js
- It should the freeze and Atom Helper process hits 100% CPU and never recovers.
